    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord
                        Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saturday Evening,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 12, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Lord Lyons</hi>: Your impression in regard to the
                    telegram was correct. Will you have the kindness to repeat your despatch to the
                    governor of New Brunswick, as the Chesapeake may have put into one of the ports
                    of that province?</p>
                <p>Very faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD. </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
